Invocation Name: northwestern law library
des:
The Northwestern Law Library skill provides answers to a variety of questions relating to the Pritzker Legal Research Center and legal research, more generally. Upon enabling this skill, you can ask Alexa questions such as:

"When does the library open?"
"How do I print at the library?
"Where is the library computer lab located?"
"When will a reference librarian be available?"
"How do I submit an interlibrary loan request?
"Can I use Westlaw for my summer job?"
"How do I do legislative history research?"

We're working to improve this skill over time, so please let a reference librarian know if you have any feedback or recommendations!
priv: Your requests to this skill are not shared with the skill developer.
